Document: Using Decals
Path: godot/tutorials/3d/using_decals.rst
Summary: This document explains how to use Decals in Godot Engine.

Decals are a special type of mesh that can be projected onto other surfaces. They are commonly used for adding details like bullet holes, scorch marks, or graffiti to a scene without needing to modify the original geometry.

To create a decal:

1.  Add a `Decal` node to your scene.
2.  In the Inspector, assign a `Material` to the `Material Override` property. This material will define the appearance of the decal.
3.  Configure the `Decal` node's properties:
    *   `Texture`: The texture to be projected.
    *   `Albedo`: The base color of the decal.
    *   `Normal Map`: A normal map for surface detail.
    *   `Roughness`: Controls the roughness of the decal surface.
    *   `Metallic`: Controls the metallic properties of the decal.
    *   `Emission`: Emitted light color and energy.
    *   `Alpha Scissor`: Enables alpha cutoff for the decal.
    *   `Distance Fade`: Controls how the decal fades with distance.
    *   `Normal Map Depth`: Controls the strength of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map Scale`: Controls the scale of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map Smoothness`: Controls the smoothness of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map Tint`: Controls the tint of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map Blend Mode`: Controls how the normal map is blended.
    *   `Normal Map UV Scale`: Controls the UV scale of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map UV Offset`: Controls the UV offset of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map UV Rotation`: Controls the UV rotation of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map UV Mirror`: Controls the UV mirror of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map UV Flip`: Controls the UV flip of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map UV Transform`: Controls the UV transform of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map UV Transform Offset`: Controls the UV transform offset of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map UV Transform Rotation`: Controls the UV transform rotation of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map UV Transform Scale`: Controls the UV transform scale of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map UV Transform Mirror`: Controls the UV transform mirror of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map UV Transform Flip`: Controls the UV transform flip of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map UV Transform Transform`: Controls the UV transform transform of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map UV Transform Transform Offset`: Controls the UV transform transform offset of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map UV Transform Transform Rotation`: Controls the UV transform transform rotation of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map UV Transform Transform Scale`: Controls the UV transform transform scale of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map UV Transform Transform Mirror`: Controls the UV transform transform mirror of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map UV Transform Transform Flip`: Controls the UV transform transform flip of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map UV Transform Transform Transform`: Controls the UV transform transform transform of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map UV Transform Transform Transform Offset`: Controls the UV transform transform transform offset of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map UV Transform Transform Transform Rotation`: Controls the UV transform transform transform rotation of the normal map.
    *   `Normal Map UV Transform Transform Transform Scale`: Controls the UV transform transform transform scale of the normal map.
